## SPARQL Queries for Testing

After adding the property, use these queries to verify it's working:

### Query 1: List all declarations with declarants

```sparql
PREFIX gmn: <http://example.org/gmn/>
PREFIX cidoc: <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/>

SELECT ?declaration ?declarant
WHERE {
    ?declaration a gmn:E31_5_Declaration ;
                 gmn:P70_24_indicates_declarant ?declarant .
}
```

### Query 2: Count declarations by number of declarants

```sparql
PREFIX gmn: <http://example.org/gmn/>

SELECT ?declaration (COUNT(?declarant) as ?num_declarants)
WHERE {
    ?declaration gmn:P70_24_indicates_declarant ?declarant .
}
GROUP BY ?declaration
ORDER BY DESC(?num_declarants)
```

### Query 3: Find all declarations by a specific person

```sparql
PREFIX gmn: <http://example.org/gmn/>

SELECT ?declaration ?name
WHERE {
    ?declaration a gmn:E31_5_Declaration ;
                 gmn:P1_1_has_name ?name ;
                 gmn:P70_24_indicates_declarant <http://example.org/person_marco> .
}
```

